Date:11/26/2011 7:01:13 PM
From:E_K_S
US Ecology, Inc. (ECOL)
http://finance.yahoo.com/q/ks?s=ECOL+Key+Statistics

I will add it to my watch list. ECOL has less debt than WM and is selling
around the same forward PE. The hazardous waste industry can be very profitable
as such their operating margins are quite high.

I like the water treatment angle for fracking as that could be a real growth
business. I will have to research the business more and see if this is
something they do and/or consult on. If there is some sort of future EPA
permitting requirements for treating fracking effluent, this could be the
perfect company to provide the certification.

I do know from limited experience that hazardous waste disposal requires
extensive tracking and certification of the waste disposal. Disposal permits
are filed w/ the State and Feds. The waste stream is owned by the generator and
processed through to disposal (incinerated or buried).

Hazardous waste disposal is sensitive to general economic activity. Located in
Idaho, they probably have MU and INTC as major customers.

This one will be a good one to research. Thanks for the lead.

