%BOM---------------------
Date:11/28/2011 3:27:13 PM
From:J Mako
Hi Gogo,

Say I open a bakery with a $100,000 loan from the bank and an initial seed
funding $10,000 from a VC. EV of my bakery is $110k. Business goes sour and I
have to close shop. The bank is now the first in queue to ask $100k back.

I don't understand why the $100k I owe to the bank is "imagery" and
"indefinite".

The bank may not be able to recoup the entire $100k. But from the perspective
the VC (i.e. the shareholder), his main concern is whether anything is left for
his after the bank gets their part. If the bank can't recoup 100%, the VC gets
nothing back.

Similarly, in YLO's case, the main question: is there anything left to the
shareholders after the banks and the senior debt holders are paid.

%EOM----------------------

